From e217fa4f73a2dfd91a20f6d6ed78db117293f9ca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Thompson <brandon.joseph.thompson@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 23:00:29 -0700
Subject: Patch: Add CPU/RAM/temp and network speed widgets to the Noctalia
 bar.

The system-stats readout (BarStats) only ever showed on Nacre and the flat
iNiR skins (inir/aurora/angel); Noctalia had no equivalent. Wire it into
Noctalia's right island too, ahead of status.

Add a companion network-throughput widget (BarNetSpeed / the NetSpeed
singleton): a stacked download/upload readout off /proc/net/dev deltas on
the default-route interface, alongside BarStats on Noctalia, Nacre and the
flat skins, download left of stats on Noctalia. The value column is pinned
to its widest possible reading so a B/s -> KB/s -> MB/s scale change never
reflows neighboring bar modules. Clicking either row opens a new traffic
popout (NetSpeedPopout) with rate sparklines (scaled to their own recent
peak) and the cumulative session download/upload total.

